WEBVTT

00:06.049 --> 00:09.748
You think something like this
is gonna happen again?

00:09.792 --> 00:12.534
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:12.577 --> 00:14.840
Junior year of high school,
my dad pulled some strings

00:14.884 --> 00:17.147
to get me into Sussex Prep.

00:17.191 --> 00:19.758
It was tough being one
of only a couple Black students.

00:20.672 --> 00:22.370
Maggie: What is the deal
with those two, anyway?

00:22.413 --> 00:25.590
You don't know?
Nick and Jane used to date.

00:25.634 --> 00:28.115
If I'm going to start
this business,

00:28.158 --> 00:31.553
I don't just want your money.
I want you.

00:31.596 --> 00:34.947
Nothing would make me happier
than us working together.

00:34.991 --> 00:37.211
Milo got
his wisdom teeth out.

00:37.254 --> 00:39.474
Can I send you
a list of things

00:39.517 --> 00:42.172
to put in a care package
to take to his house?

00:42.216 --> 00:44.783
♪♪

00:44.827 --> 00:46.350
What are you doing here?

00:46.394 --> 00:48.004
I'm here to get Milo back.

00:51.094 --> 00:52.661
Mom! Mom!

00:52.704 --> 00:55.359
I cannot get on a plane
back to France right now.

00:55.403 --> 00:57.709
She's gonna be fine,
and you're doing great.

00:57.753 --> 00:59.581
You're not even
listening to me![ Door slams ]

00:59.624 --> 01:01.409
He's a dead man.
Yeah.

01:01.452 --> 01:03.498
Turns out, I amgoing to prison
'cause D's gonna ask me

01:03.541 --> 01:05.195
to kill him and send him back
in little pieces.

01:05.239 --> 01:07.328
Poor kid. I hope
she lets him stay long enough

01:07.371 --> 01:08.807
to at least get
a good night of sleep.

01:08.851 --> 01:12.159
Nope. I say send him back
to France as soon as possible.

01:12.202 --> 01:14.117
What? Did you not
miss him at all?

01:14.161 --> 01:15.640
Of course
I missed him, but I...[ Door opens ]

01:15.684 --> 01:17.773
Mom! I came here so I could
figure things out with Milo!

01:17.816 --> 01:19.992
...can't believe
she's being so hard on you.

01:20.036 --> 01:21.516
Will you please
stop yelling?

01:21.559 --> 01:24.214
You know I cannot understand
fast French.

01:24.258 --> 01:25.302
[ Sighs ]
[ Whispering ]
You've got this.

01:25.346 --> 01:27.130
You are being
so unfair!

01:27.174 --> 01:28.349
[ Door slams ]

01:28.392 --> 01:30.351
Of course
I love having him back.

01:30.394 --> 01:33.267
What I don't love is him
groveling, going over there

01:33.310 --> 01:36.270
trying to win that
cheating cheater Milo back.

01:36.313 --> 01:38.620
Little douchebag
doesn't deserve our Danny.

01:38.663 --> 01:39.969
No, he does not.

01:40.012 --> 01:41.144
But if you bring that up,

01:41.188 --> 01:42.754
I would leave the D-bag
out of it.

01:42.798 --> 01:44.321
He's not thinking clearly.

01:44.365 --> 01:47.063
It's his first love.
Of course he isn't.

01:47.107 --> 01:49.109
If he was, he would tell
that lying sack of --

01:49.152 --> 01:50.893
Shabbat!

01:50.936 --> 01:53.896
And that, Margaret,
is how a Bar Mitzvah works.

01:53.939 --> 01:57.552
It's weird that you asked me
about that, but, uh...

01:57.595 --> 01:59.771
Hey. How'd it go?

01:59.815 --> 02:02.426
She has never been
so mad at me.

02:02.470 --> 02:04.472
I'm definitely gonna pay for
this when I get back home.

02:04.515 --> 02:07.170
Sorry, man.
[ Clicks tongue ]

02:07.214 --> 02:09.041
Need a ride
to the airport, dude?[ Milk pours ]

02:09.085 --> 02:11.218
Uh, no.
Not yet, actually.

02:11.261 --> 02:13.916
She's letting me stay for Spring
Break so I can get Milo back.

02:13.959 --> 02:16.266
Huh.

02:16.310 --> 02:17.963
Huh.

02:18.007 --> 02:19.835
That's great.Yeah.

02:19.878 --> 02:21.924
♪♪

02:30.237 --> 02:31.586
Maggie: Thank you.

02:37.896 --> 02:39.811
Hey!
Hello, there.

02:39.855 --> 02:42.031
Hi!
What's going on?

02:42.074 --> 02:44.120
I have a gift
from the station's owner,

02:44.164 --> 02:47.036
for WZLN's star employee.

02:47.079 --> 02:49.995
Mr. Cutler? Why is he
giving me your phone?

02:50.039 --> 02:52.215
No, no, no.
That's not the gift.

02:52.259 --> 02:53.303
Push right here.

02:55.218 --> 02:57.264
[ Beeping ]

02:57.307 --> 02:58.874
[ Engine starts ]

02:58.917 --> 03:00.223
[ Chuckles ]

03:00.267 --> 03:03.139
Why did your phone
just start that car?

03:03.183 --> 03:06.142
Because that
is Michael Cutler's gift

03:06.186 --> 03:08.188
to the station's
highest-rated host.

03:08.231 --> 03:11.234
That sweet ride is yours!
[ Chuckles ]

03:11.278 --> 03:14.106
As soon as you program
the digital-key feature

03:14.150 --> 03:16.021
to connect with your phone,
because --

03:16.065 --> 03:17.588
Actually,
I need mine back.

03:17.632 --> 03:19.503
Wow!

03:19.547 --> 03:20.591
[ Both laugh ]

03:20.635 --> 03:22.637
I know, right?!

03:22.680 --> 03:24.291
Remember when
you wanted to fire me?

03:24.334 --> 03:26.380
Oh, hey, you know what?
Be nice to me.

03:26.423 --> 03:28.469
The only thing I ever got
from this company is a mug.

03:28.512 --> 03:29.905
-Oh.
-Maybe if you made your job

03:29.948 --> 03:31.559
as much of a priority
as you do your appearance,

03:31.602 --> 03:32.951
you'd have a car by now.

03:32.995 --> 03:34.649
With a vanity plate,
I'm sure.

03:34.692 --> 03:38.348
Hey, Nick. Weren't you supposed
to be on vacation this week?

03:38.392 --> 03:40.785
Starts tomorrow.Not a moment too soon.

03:40.829 --> 03:43.092
Shall we?

03:43.135 --> 03:45.007
Oh, we shall.
Good luck.

03:45.050 --> 03:47.444
Route 9's backed up
all the way to Worcester.

03:47.488 --> 03:50.230
Regina: It's near Boston Common,
Dad. Can't beat that.

03:50.273 --> 03:51.927
And how cute would it be
having our sign up

03:51.970 --> 03:53.450
on that sweet little
awning?

03:53.494 --> 03:56.192
Come on.
That space is way too small!

03:56.236 --> 03:57.889
You got menow.

03:57.933 --> 03:59.587
With your talent,
once we're up and running,

03:59.630 --> 04:01.197
we are gonna be
unstoppable.

04:01.241 --> 04:04.548
You gotta start
thinking bigger, Gigi.

04:05.462 --> 04:07.421
Alright, alright.
Let's talk about that sign.

04:07.464 --> 04:09.031
What should we put on it?

04:09.074 --> 04:11.338
[ Exhales sharply ]
Well, uh, Val and I were

04:11.381 --> 04:13.209
actually brainstorming names
the other day.

04:13.253 --> 04:16.168
What do you think of
"Ease Catering"?

04:16.212 --> 04:19.563
"Put your mind at Ease,
we got the food covered."

04:19.607 --> 04:21.130
It's a great tagline.

04:21.173 --> 04:22.740
Thank you.
That's what we thought --

04:22.784 --> 04:23.959
But I don't know
about the name.

04:24.002 --> 04:25.743
They say most
successful companies

04:25.787 --> 04:28.877
have a "teh"
or a "keh" sound.

04:28.920 --> 04:32.663
Mm. Don't tell that to Apple
or Disney or Google.

04:32.707 --> 04:33.882
Huh?
Nothing.

04:33.925 --> 04:35.275
[ Cellphone buzzes ]Oh.

04:35.318 --> 04:36.580
Katherine says they have

04:36.624 --> 04:38.756
our articles of incorporation
ready to sign.

04:38.800 --> 04:40.323
That's what
I'm talking about.

04:40.367 --> 04:41.585
[ Chuckles ]Let's go make this official.

04:41.629 --> 04:43.021
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

04:43.065 --> 04:44.849
Ah, she said
to stop by at lunch

04:44.893 --> 04:46.851
and Carter
will walk us through it.

04:46.895 --> 04:47.896
Fantastic.

04:49.071 --> 04:51.203
Yeah.

04:51.247 --> 04:52.814
What is it?

04:52.857 --> 04:55.947
It's just...
[ Sighs ]

04:55.991 --> 04:58.080
Katherine's office
is above Someday.

04:58.123 --> 05:00.256
Or where Someday
used to be.

05:00.300 --> 05:01.997
It'll be my first time back
since we closed.

05:02.040 --> 05:04.086
[ Clears throat ]

05:04.129 --> 05:06.349
I know that was so hard,
losing your dream restaurant.

05:06.393 --> 05:08.220
Yeah, it was.

05:08.264 --> 05:12.050
But the --
the timing was off, and...

05:12.094 --> 05:15.184
You know, sometimes,
I still wonder if...

05:15.227 --> 05:16.794
If what?

05:19.493 --> 05:21.277
No.
It doesn't matter.

05:21.321 --> 05:24.193
All good things
come to an end, right?

05:24.236 --> 05:26.761
Okay. Let's try expanding
our search area.

05:26.804 --> 05:29.285
[ Keyboard clacking ]

05:29.329 --> 05:35.030
♪♪

05:36.466 --> 05:38.120
Feel better?

05:38.163 --> 05:39.687
A little.

05:39.730 --> 05:43.865
But, um, I still have no idea
what I'm gonna do about Milo.

05:43.908 --> 05:46.607
The best I can come up with
is to stand outside his house

05:46.650 --> 05:49.566
with a boombox
and play some Peter Gabriel.

05:49.610 --> 05:52.700
But, um, maybe
I've just been watching

05:52.743 --> 05:54.092
too many
John Hughes movies.

05:56.181 --> 05:58.183
M'kay, that's --
that's Cameron Crowe,

05:58.227 --> 05:59.968
but I'm gonna
let it slide.

06:00.011 --> 06:02.449
What do I do?

06:02.492 --> 06:04.929
Help me out here,
sensei.

06:04.973 --> 06:08.890
Well,
since you're asking...

06:08.933 --> 06:13.503
we could just hang out,
play video games all day,

06:13.547 --> 06:17.159
eat the burgers and tacos that
you're not getting in France.

06:17.202 --> 06:18.813
And we forget
about that jerk

06:18.856 --> 06:21.859
who thinks it's okay
to smash faces with other boys.

06:21.903 --> 06:25.472
I-I can't just forget
about him.

06:26.908 --> 06:30.172
Well, we can do the otherthing
that '80s movies taught us.

06:30.215 --> 06:32.870
You can make him
insanely jealous

06:32.914 --> 06:35.351
of the thing
he can no longer have,

06:35.395 --> 06:38.049
because you are
no longer his.

06:38.093 --> 06:41.183
You go over there, you're
gonna dump his sorry butt,

06:41.226 --> 06:42.532
and you're gonna do it
looking like

06:42.576 --> 06:44.360
a delicious piece
of man candy.

06:44.404 --> 06:45.970
Now, that...

06:46.014 --> 06:48.364
that's classic John Hughes.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.235
[ The Cure's
"Just Like Heaven" plays ]

06:50.279 --> 06:52.281
And you think
that'll make me feel better?

06:52.324 --> 06:54.370
Yeah. There's only
one way to find out.[ Slap on back ]

06:55.806 --> 06:58.374
For the first time,
I am glad that my roommate

06:58.418 --> 07:01.812
has more beauty products than
all the Kardashians combined.

07:01.856 --> 07:03.074
You go to town in there.

07:03.118 --> 07:04.336
By the time you're out,

07:04.380 --> 07:08.645
I'll have this thing
up and ready...

07:08.689 --> 07:11.256
[ Grunts ]
...to press.

07:11.300 --> 07:13.520
Yeah? You seem like
you know how to use that.

07:13.563 --> 07:15.565
[ Laughs ]

07:15.609 --> 07:18.612
I am so sorry
I had to cancel our lunch.

07:18.655 --> 07:20.309
Katherine was able
to get an appointment

07:20.352 --> 07:23.443
for Theo and his therapist, and
she asked for us all to come.

07:23.486 --> 07:25.706
He's just been so anxious
since Katherine's accident.

07:25.749 --> 07:27.098
Oh, my goodness.
Of course.

07:27.142 --> 07:28.665
Eddie,
I completely understand.

07:28.709 --> 07:30.058
Well, thank you.

07:30.101 --> 07:32.364
And to make it up to you,
I got you some extra guac.

07:32.408 --> 07:33.801
Not the little one.
The biggie.

07:33.844 --> 07:35.367
Ooh!
Yeah.

07:35.411 --> 07:37.718
It's too bad, though,
because I was gonna force us

07:37.761 --> 07:39.589
to be the obnoxious couple
that snuggled

07:39.633 --> 07:40.634
on the same side
of the booth.

07:40.677 --> 07:42.200
I love that.

07:42.244 --> 07:45.073
And I promise, we will annoy
all the restaurant patrons

07:45.116 --> 07:48.250
with our adorable smugness
another time.

07:48.293 --> 07:52.646
You know, maybe us missing lunch
is for the best.

07:52.689 --> 07:54.952
How so?Because instead of lunch,

07:54.996 --> 07:58.086
perhaps we could do
a romantic dinner.

07:58.129 --> 08:00.218
At my place?

08:00.262 --> 08:02.873
We could dress up,
or we could not...

08:02.917 --> 08:04.527
dress at all.

08:04.571 --> 08:08.009
That is, if you want
to spend the night.

08:08.052 --> 08:12.535
Yeah. Sure.
I mean...really?

08:12.579 --> 08:14.929
Extremelyreally.
Mm-hmm.

08:14.972 --> 08:16.365
Great.

08:16.408 --> 08:18.062
I will see you
tonight, then.

08:18.106 --> 08:19.499
Okay.

08:19.542 --> 08:25.026
♪♪

08:25.069 --> 08:30.553
♪♪

08:30.597 --> 08:33.121
Whatcha doin'?

08:33.164 --> 08:35.297
This morning, I told Dr. Heller
about how I freaked out

08:35.340 --> 08:38.256
over your Yale interview,
how I think it was because

08:38.300 --> 08:40.911
of what happened
when I went to Sussex Prep.

08:40.955 --> 08:42.217
Sounds intense.
Yeah.

08:42.260 --> 08:44.654
So now I'm looking up
old classmates.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.308
[ Keyboard clacks ]

08:46.351 --> 08:51.095
Heller thinks it might be good
for me to visit the campus.

08:51.139 --> 08:53.750
Thinking about ripping off
the Band-Aid and going today.

08:53.794 --> 08:56.100
Wow. You really did
have hair once.

08:56.144 --> 08:58.320
Oh, yeah.
Even more than you.

08:58.363 --> 09:00.365
So cherish that, 'cause
it probably ain't gonna last.

09:00.409 --> 09:03.107
[ Chuckles ] Nah.
These follicles are invincible.

09:04.848 --> 09:06.371
God.
You weren't kidding.

09:06.415 --> 09:08.896
You were really
the only Black kid, huh?

09:08.939 --> 09:12.900
Yeah. It was me and
Dre Washington. In our grade.

09:12.943 --> 09:15.032
And check this out.

09:15.076 --> 09:16.860
Apparently,
he's still there.

09:16.904 --> 09:19.559
Oh, they got a brother
as Vice Principal.

09:19.602 --> 09:21.604
That's what's up. Huh.
True.

09:23.432 --> 09:26.087
I just can't believe
he'd work there after
everything we went through.

09:28.872 --> 09:30.482
What didyou go through?

09:30.526 --> 09:33.747
♪♪

09:33.790 --> 09:36.750
Alright, Colin, prepare
to have your mind blown

09:36.793 --> 09:39.840
by my post-breakup
comfort-food creation.

09:39.883 --> 09:41.102
[ Sighs ]

09:41.145 --> 09:42.973
Hamburger patty,
topped with hash browns,

09:43.017 --> 09:44.714
sandwiched between two waffles.

09:44.758 --> 09:45.759
The hashburgaffle.

09:45.802 --> 09:47.630
[ Laughter ]Hello?

09:48.805 --> 09:51.939
Oh, you're back
already, huh?

09:51.982 --> 09:53.288
How'd it go?
You okay?

09:53.331 --> 09:54.506
Uh...

09:58.293 --> 09:59.511
Milo.

10:01.035 --> 10:04.125
Uh, so,
we are back together.

10:04.168 --> 10:05.387
[ Chuckles ]

10:05.430 --> 10:06.823
♪ Just like heaven

10:12.873 --> 10:15.179
Rome: And then, of course,
there was the usual stuff.

10:15.223 --> 10:17.094
You know, the teacher
not picking me

10:17.138 --> 10:18.487
when I had the answer
to a question,

10:18.530 --> 10:20.271
but then they'd single me out
so that I can explain

10:20.315 --> 10:22.709
to the class what the
"African-American community"

10:22.752 --> 10:24.580
had to say
about a subject,

10:24.624 --> 10:27.583
telling me how impressed they
were with how well-spoken I was.

10:27.627 --> 10:29.454
Yeah, I've gotten that
a few times.

10:29.498 --> 10:31.848
It's like, bro, I grew up
five blocks from you.

10:31.892 --> 10:33.720
Why would I talk
differently?

10:33.763 --> 10:36.113
It is exhausting.

10:36.157 --> 10:38.463
Yeah. And that was
just the faculty, man.

10:38.507 --> 10:40.378
Kids are much worse.

10:40.422 --> 10:44.208
My senior year,
during Black History Month,

10:44.252 --> 10:45.688
these guys thought
it would be funny

10:45.732 --> 10:48.256
to hang a "Whites Only" sign
on the water fountain.

10:48.299 --> 10:51.041
Oh, my God.
What did you do?

10:51.085 --> 10:53.130
There was this guy,
Mr. Dennings.

10:53.174 --> 10:54.436
He was
my history teacher.

10:54.479 --> 10:56.003
I told him everything,
'cause I thought for sure

10:56.046 --> 10:57.787
he'd do something about it
'cause now I finally had proof

10:57.831 --> 10:59.354
of what
had been happening.

10:59.397 --> 11:02.052
He just -- [Chuckles] --

11:02.096 --> 11:04.707
He just took the sign
and threw it away.

11:04.751 --> 11:06.317
Tyrell: Man.

11:06.361 --> 11:08.755
I'd never felt more betrayed
in my life.

11:08.798 --> 11:11.018
I remember him straightening
his stupid bow tie

11:11.061 --> 11:13.324
and telling me it would be best
to just let it go.

11:13.368 --> 11:14.761
♪♪

11:14.804 --> 11:17.285
Said it would only get worse
if I made any noise.

11:17.328 --> 11:19.940
So I didn't.

11:19.983 --> 11:22.072
I just kept my mouth shut
on that day.

11:22.116 --> 11:23.944
And every day
after that.

11:23.987 --> 11:26.468
♪♪

11:26.511 --> 11:29.732
You know what? If you're going,
I'm going with you.

11:29.776 --> 11:31.342
No, man, it's okay.

11:31.386 --> 11:33.344
I-I-I think this is something
I need to do on my own.

11:35.956 --> 11:37.218
Thank you.

11:37.261 --> 11:40.787
♪♪

11:40.830 --> 11:43.311
Thanks again
for coming, Susan.
Of course.

11:43.354 --> 11:45.139
And, you know,
it's really helpful to have

11:45.182 --> 11:46.749
so much support
from both parents.

11:46.793 --> 11:48.055
You're doing a great job.

11:48.098 --> 11:49.360
I'll see you
next week, Theo.

11:49.404 --> 11:50.840
-Thanks. Bye.
-Bye.

11:50.884 --> 11:52.624
Katherine: Bye.Eddie: Well, I should
head out, too.

11:52.668 --> 11:55.279
Actually, can't you stay
a little longer, Dad?

11:55.323 --> 11:56.933
I started
the Kylo Ren ship,

11:56.977 --> 12:00.415
and it's like a thousand pieces,
so I need an assistant.

12:00.458 --> 12:01.938
Oh, T, that's
gonna take forever,

12:01.982 --> 12:03.374
and your dad can't stay.

12:03.418 --> 12:05.725
He has a-a date tonight
with Anna.

12:05.768 --> 12:08.989
You know what? It's okay.
I can push it.

12:09.032 --> 12:10.730
Awesome!
It's on the table.

12:12.775 --> 12:14.472
Are you sure?
You don't have to cancel.

12:14.516 --> 12:15.735
It's just...

12:15.778 --> 12:19.216
No. Theo needs me here.
Anna will understand.

12:20.087 --> 12:21.479
Okay.

12:21.523 --> 12:25.222
♪♪

12:25.266 --> 12:26.833
Danny: He will.

12:26.876 --> 12:29.270
Milo: Gross!
You got any tissues?

12:29.313 --> 12:32.969
Alright. Stop everything
you're doing and behold.

12:33.013 --> 12:33.970
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:34.014 --> 12:36.712
Boom. Boom.

12:36.756 --> 12:39.323
I-Is that a waffle
as a bun?

12:39.367 --> 12:41.717
[ Chuckles ]
Yes, it is, Milo.

12:41.761 --> 12:44.285
Feel free to eat around
the delicious parts.

12:44.328 --> 12:47.549
Do you have any tissues?
Milo's allergic to dogs.

12:47.592 --> 12:48.985
[ Hushed ]
Of course he is.

12:49.029 --> 12:50.465
Milo: What?[ Normal voice ]
Yeah. Yeah.

12:50.508 --> 12:52.206
Yeah, I think I've got some
on a shelf in the bathroom.

12:52.249 --> 12:53.773
Okay.
I'll be right back.

12:57.428 --> 12:59.082
[ Door closes ]Dude,
what the hell happened?

12:59.126 --> 13:00.823
We had a plan.
It was solid.

13:00.867 --> 13:03.086
You were gonna go over
there, you were gonna
dump his cheating ass.

13:03.130 --> 13:05.828
H-He told me he loved me
and begged me to forgive him.

13:05.872 --> 13:07.221
Of course,
he's gonna say that.

13:07.264 --> 13:08.788
Have youseen
your amazing hair?

13:08.831 --> 13:10.615
You're like a half-French
Erik Estrada.

13:10.659 --> 13:12.835
You can't let him off the hook
like that, Dan.

13:12.879 --> 13:14.837
You have no idea
how hard it was

13:14.881 --> 13:17.361
to be separated
for six months, okay?

13:17.405 --> 13:20.451
He regrets it. Believe me.
And I'm letting it go.

13:20.495 --> 13:23.628
You're just setting yourself up
for more heartbreak, kid.

13:23.672 --> 13:25.239
You can't trust
that guy.

13:25.282 --> 13:27.415
You think
I don't know that?

13:27.458 --> 13:30.070
Yeah, obviously I can't
totally trust him right now,

13:30.113 --> 13:32.159
but we're building
that trust back.

13:32.202 --> 13:33.247
That's the whole point
of this.

13:33.290 --> 13:35.249
There's no way
that I'm gonna le--

13:35.292 --> 13:37.860
That is why they call it
a menstrual cycle.

13:37.904 --> 13:39.514
Now, who is hungry?

13:39.557 --> 13:41.864
A-Actually, I'm gonna head out.
My allergies are acting up.

13:43.431 --> 13:46.434
Oh. Okay.
Talk to you later?

13:46.477 --> 13:47.696
Milo: Uh-huh.[ Door opens ]

13:47.739 --> 13:48.915
Have a good one, Milo!

13:48.958 --> 13:50.177
[ Door closes ]

13:50.220 --> 13:51.961
I knew you were
a cat person.

13:53.310 --> 13:56.792
♪♪

13:56.836 --> 13:58.098
That was rude. No?

14:00.665 --> 14:04.495
Uh, Anonymous in Charlestown,
you are "in the room."

14:04.539 --> 14:07.629
Caller:
Um, hi, Dr. Bloom.

14:07.672 --> 14:10.762
So, I'm a single mom
of two little ones,

14:10.806 --> 14:12.547
and they are the greatest joy
in my life.

14:12.590 --> 14:14.027
[ Chuckles][ Chuckles ]

14:14.070 --> 14:15.985
I work days, and I'm also
going to night school

14:16.029 --> 14:17.682
to become a nurse.

14:17.726 --> 14:20.424
Wow.
That is all very impressive.

14:20.468 --> 14:21.773
Thank you.

14:21.817 --> 14:24.559
I'm lucky that my family
helps with my kids.

14:24.602 --> 14:28.955
But the thing is...
I'm pregnant again.

14:28.998 --> 14:31.348
No one even knows yet.

14:31.392 --> 14:34.612
This wasn't planned,
and I just know that I can't

14:34.656 --> 14:37.224
give my kids everything
they need if I have this baby.

14:37.267 --> 14:38.834
[ Voice breaking ]
I'd have to quit school,

14:38.878 --> 14:40.618
which is something
I'm doing for their future.

14:40.662 --> 14:42.925
And, well, I just --

14:42.969 --> 14:45.058
I don't have it in me to --

14:45.101 --> 14:46.929
[ Sniffles] Oh, God.
I'm sorry. I just...

14:46.973 --> 14:49.584
No. That's -- That's okay.
That's...okay.

14:49.627 --> 14:52.152
Um, that sounds overwhelming.

14:52.195 --> 14:54.502
It is.

14:54.545 --> 14:58.245
Which is why I've decided
not to keep it.

14:58.288 --> 15:00.290
It's definitely
the best decision,

15:00.334 --> 15:03.946
but I don't know
how to tell my family.

15:03.990 --> 15:05.600
They're religious,

15:05.643 --> 15:09.256
and I'm afraid
they will think less of me.

15:09.299 --> 15:12.999
I know that...

15:13.042 --> 15:16.176
ending a pregnancy
can be delicate...

15:16.219 --> 15:18.395
which is all the more reason
to surround yourself

15:18.439 --> 15:21.050
with people
who are supportive of you.

15:21.094 --> 15:25.011
Do you have anyone
you can lean on?

15:25.054 --> 15:29.711
Caller: Maybe some of
my friends, but I'm not sure.

15:29.754 --> 15:31.321
I understand.

15:31.365 --> 15:34.934
Uh, well, we can give you
access to resources...

15:34.977 --> 15:38.067
like the closest safe clinic
for you to go to.

15:38.111 --> 15:39.851
Caller: Thank you.[ Telephone beeps ]

15:39.895 --> 15:42.028
Jane's assistant: Jane, I have
Mr. Cutler on the line for you.

15:42.071 --> 15:44.117
Caller: Do you think I should
tell my family about it?

15:44.160 --> 15:47.424
Maggie: I think you should do
whatever is best for you.

15:47.468 --> 15:49.774
This is Jane.

15:49.818 --> 15:51.298
What do you think
would happen

15:51.341 --> 15:54.301
if you were to nottell
your family?

15:54.344 --> 15:56.564
Caller: [ Sighs]
I-I'm not sure.

15:56.607 --> 16:00.698
I guess I hadn't thought
about it because...

16:00.742 --> 16:03.832
I want to be able
to tell them everything.

16:03.875 --> 16:08.054
Well, it's your right to keep
this private, if you want to.

16:08.097 --> 16:11.361
Thank you.
That really helps.

16:11.405 --> 16:15.409
Good.
Stay on the line for resources.

16:15.452 --> 16:18.194
And that is our show for today.
Thank you for listening.

16:18.238 --> 16:19.804
[ Click ]

16:19.848 --> 16:22.329
Maggie, I need to see you
in my office. Now.

16:22.372 --> 16:27.943
♪♪

16:27.987 --> 16:31.468
[ Headphones clatter ]

16:31.512 --> 16:32.992
[ Sighs ]

16:39.650 --> 16:42.262
Come on, Jane. What would you
have me do? She needed help.

16:42.305 --> 16:44.525
Maggie, you cannot
give your listener

16:44.568 --> 16:46.135
that kind of information.

16:46.179 --> 16:48.094
I give resources
to all my callers.

16:48.137 --> 16:50.531
Not when it comes
to that subject.

16:50.574 --> 16:54.361
Talk radio has one of the most
conservative audiences,

16:54.404 --> 16:56.102
and if you think
they're buttoned up,

16:56.145 --> 16:59.801
you haven't met Mr. Cutler, who
owns the station and your show.

16:59.844 --> 17:02.978
Yes, obviously, I know that
Mr. Cutler is conservative.

17:03.022 --> 17:06.677
We're grown women,
and we call him Mr.Cutler.

17:06.721 --> 17:08.505
It is an easy fix.

17:08.549 --> 17:10.203
Your producers just need
to screen the calls better,

17:10.246 --> 17:13.206
and the next time the...
A-word comes up,

17:13.249 --> 17:14.946
they're not gonna
take it.

17:14.990 --> 17:16.818
They most certainly
are going to take it

17:16.861 --> 17:20.169
if a call comes in
about abortion.

17:20.213 --> 17:21.736
Jane, come on.

17:21.779 --> 17:24.304
You are the one who told me
that to make my show meaningful,

17:24.347 --> 17:27.350
I needed to connect to people
on a deeper level.

17:27.394 --> 17:29.352
I can't think of anything
that goes deeper than this.

17:29.396 --> 17:31.354
I mean, what would you do
in my situation?

17:31.398 --> 17:36.316
It is best to just avoid a topic
that is so political.

17:36.359 --> 17:41.451
Except it is not political.
It's personal.

17:41.495 --> 17:43.932
For that woman who called
and for every single person

17:43.975 --> 17:46.891
who's ever had to
face that decision.

17:46.935 --> 17:49.459
Supporting those women
is way more important

17:49.503 --> 17:51.635
than cowing to some
male executive's wishes --

17:51.679 --> 17:53.724
I support women.

17:53.768 --> 17:57.163
I have supported women
my whole career.

17:57.206 --> 18:00.644
You and I -- we managed
to infiltrate a boys' club,

18:00.688 --> 18:02.777
and in order
to stay here,

18:02.820 --> 18:05.823
we have to make
some concessions.

18:05.867 --> 18:10.176
Talking about this on the air
is going to have consequences.

18:10.219 --> 18:12.917
I wish that were not the case,
Maggie, but it's the reality.

18:15.181 --> 18:17.139
Then I will face
the consequences.

18:17.183 --> 18:20.838
♪♪

18:20.882 --> 18:22.013
Okay, then.

18:23.928 --> 18:25.321
Okay.

18:25.365 --> 18:26.801
Hm.

18:26.844 --> 18:35.375
♪♪

18:35.418 --> 18:44.166
♪♪

18:44.210 --> 18:48.431
[ Bell ringing ]

18:48.475 --> 18:50.564
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:50.607 --> 18:55.656
♪♪

18:55.699 --> 19:00.965
♪♪

19:01.009 --> 19:02.532
[ Laughter ]

19:02.576 --> 19:04.404
Young man: Hey, Clark.
Here he comes.

19:04.447 --> 19:06.232
[ Laughter ]

19:06.275 --> 19:07.798
Look at his face!

19:07.842 --> 19:10.323
[ Laughter ]

19:10.366 --> 19:13.152
Oh! I-It's Mr. Dennings!
Run!

19:13.195 --> 19:15.893
♪♪

19:15.937 --> 19:18.940
Mr. Dennings: Just let it go.
It'll only make things worse.

19:20.246 --> 19:22.900
Man: Rome? Rome?

19:22.944 --> 19:24.424
Rome Howard?

19:25.468 --> 19:27.296
Dre Washington.

19:28.776 --> 19:30.212
How are you, man?

19:30.256 --> 19:32.040
I'm so glad
you asked to drop by.

19:35.043 --> 19:37.088
Good to see you, man.
Yeah.

19:37.132 --> 19:39.395
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

19:39.439 --> 19:41.528
♪ I started drinking...

19:41.571 --> 19:43.573
Hey. I was just
thinking about you.

19:43.617 --> 19:46.315
Do you prefer "can barely
see each other" candlelight

19:46.359 --> 19:48.317
or "fire hazard"?

19:48.361 --> 19:49.927
And please say fire hazard,
because I think it'd be

19:49.971 --> 19:51.277
really fun to live
on the edge tonight.

19:51.320 --> 19:53.235
That is actually
why I'm calling.

19:53.279 --> 19:56.717
I am so sorry,
but it seems like Theo

19:56.760 --> 19:59.502
really needs me to hang
a while longer.

19:59.546 --> 20:01.939
Oh. Yeah, okay.
Of course.

20:01.983 --> 20:06.335
Do you -- Do you want to
just come over for dessert?

20:06.379 --> 20:09.208
Actually, I'm gonna spend
the night over here.

20:09.251 --> 20:11.862
This morning's session
was hard for Theo,

20:11.906 --> 20:14.691
brought up some stuff,
so...

20:14.735 --> 20:16.171
I'm sorry to hear that.

20:16.215 --> 20:18.347
Uh, do...
whatever you need to do.

20:18.391 --> 20:20.828
It's just --

20:20.871 --> 20:25.093
To be honest, I'm just --
I'm starting to wonder if...

20:25.136 --> 20:27.443
If what?

20:27.487 --> 20:30.664
If they make "Dad of the Year"
awards big enough for you.

20:30.707 --> 20:31.795
[ Chuckles ]

20:31.839 --> 20:33.319
That's very kind.

20:33.362 --> 20:36.235
And we are gonna rain-check
this one, too. I promise.

20:37.497 --> 20:39.325
Okay. Great.

20:41.457 --> 20:43.067
Look at you!
You look good incorporated!

20:43.111 --> 20:44.417
And you do, too.
Yeah.

20:44.460 --> 20:46.854
Oh, I wish
we could celebrate.
Ah.

20:46.897 --> 20:49.291
But if we're meeting
the real-estate agent at 1:00,

20:49.335 --> 20:51.119
we're already late.

20:51.162 --> 20:52.512
Where are we heading,
anyway?

20:52.555 --> 20:55.036
Well, we won't be late,
because...

20:55.079 --> 20:56.864
we are already here.

20:58.518 --> 21:01.303
Surprise!

21:01.347 --> 21:03.262
What? Surprise
it's my old restaurant?

21:03.305 --> 21:05.612
Yeah.
It's available again.What?

21:05.655 --> 21:08.571
This morning, you seemed so sad
about losing Someday,

21:08.615 --> 21:10.312
I called up
the building's management.

21:10.356 --> 21:13.141
The new tenants couldn't make
a go of it, so it's up for rent.

21:13.184 --> 21:16.013
How amazing is that?
We're touring it.

21:16.057 --> 21:18.320
What?
No, Dad, that's crazy.

21:18.364 --> 21:22.063
Why? It's a great space.
It's a beautiful location.

21:22.106 --> 21:24.021
You already know it
inside and out.

21:24.065 --> 21:25.632
I mean, it's kind of
perfect, right?

21:25.675 --> 21:27.068
N-No. [ Chuckles ]

21:27.111 --> 21:28.722
We're --
That's a restaurant.

21:28.765 --> 21:29.897
We're doing catering.

21:29.940 --> 21:32.465
I know that. You can
reopen the restaurant.

21:32.508 --> 21:35.076
We can base the catering
business out of here.

21:35.119 --> 21:37.339
Don't be scared
to dream big.

21:37.383 --> 21:40.821
I'm not scared. I'm --
And it's not about dreaming big.

21:40.864 --> 21:42.605
I-It's -- I-I just...

21:45.391 --> 21:48.568
Okay, look.
I-I can't do this, okay?

21:48.611 --> 21:49.960
Enjoy your tour.

21:50.004 --> 21:59.056
♪♪

21:59.100 --> 22:01.102
Gary: Heard anything
from the cat lover yet?

22:06.629 --> 22:09.676
Danny: Oh, my God.
Oh, my God!

22:09.719 --> 22:12.156
Milo heard us talking
when he was in the bathroom.

22:12.200 --> 22:14.811
He heard you say
I should dump him!

22:14.855 --> 22:17.597
Now this is all messed up again,
and it's yourfault!

22:17.640 --> 22:19.207
Alright.
Obviously, I didn't --

22:19.250 --> 22:21.078
I didn't mean
for him to hear that.

22:21.122 --> 22:24.299
But, dude, honestly,
I did you a favor.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.475
Come on.
You deserve so much better.

22:26.519 --> 22:28.651
That is easy
for you to say.

22:28.695 --> 22:32.699
How many other openly gay kids
do you know?

22:32.742 --> 22:34.527
Exactly two in Boston and --

22:34.570 --> 22:37.747
Oh, yeah, yeah,
none in Paris,

22:37.791 --> 22:39.793
which is the same amount
I know!

22:39.836 --> 22:41.751
Milo made one mistake,

22:41.795 --> 22:44.580
and I would think
you, of all people,

22:44.624 --> 22:46.713
would understand
that doesn't mean

22:46.756 --> 22:49.716
he should never get
a second chance!

22:49.759 --> 22:51.457
You know what?

22:51.500 --> 22:53.415
Sophie was totally right
about you.

22:53.459 --> 22:56.984
♪♪

22:57.027 --> 22:59.856
Danny, come back. We just --
We can fix this!

23:01.858 --> 23:03.033
Dan!

23:03.077 --> 23:07.516
♪♪

23:07.560 --> 23:09.213
[ Sighs ]

23:13.653 --> 23:16.395
Before I go,
I want to share something

23:16.438 --> 23:19.267
that came up in my morning show.

23:19.310 --> 23:21.878
I-I bring this up
not because I'm trying

23:21.922 --> 23:25.142
to convince anyone of anything.

23:25.186 --> 23:26.709
It's actually the opposite.

23:26.753 --> 23:31.148
I-I want to talk about this
because I felt pressured not to.

23:32.759 --> 23:36.110
But I am ready
to face any consequences

23:36.153 --> 23:38.634
that come of what
I'm about to say.

23:43.117 --> 23:45.598
Which is that...

23:48.122 --> 23:51.386
...I had an abortion last year,

23:51.430 --> 23:57.218
and it was 100% the right choice
for me at the time.

23:57.261 --> 24:03.833
♪♪

24:03.877 --> 24:05.269
I also made that choice

24:05.313 --> 24:09.273
knowing that I want
to be a mom someday.

24:09.317 --> 24:12.059
I always knew that I would want
to be a parent

24:12.102 --> 24:16.411
when I am prepared for it
physically, emotionally,

24:16.455 --> 24:18.195
professionally, and financially.

24:18.239 --> 24:20.763
And -- And those
are just a fraction

24:20.807 --> 24:23.026
of the many complicated
circumstances

24:23.070 --> 24:25.333
around mychoice
to have an abortion,

24:25.376 --> 24:28.292
but every single person
who faces that choice

24:28.336 --> 24:30.556
has their own
unique circumstances,

24:30.599 --> 24:34.037
and that is what makes
that decision personal to them.

24:34.081 --> 24:36.518
Not political.

24:36.562 --> 24:38.999
Personal.

24:39.042 --> 24:43.743
It is no one else's place
to judge or shame any woman

24:43.786 --> 24:45.658
for deciding
what is best for her.

24:45.701 --> 24:50.227
♪♪

24:50.271 --> 24:54.493
So, i-if you need information
on abortion or contraception,

24:54.536 --> 24:56.799
please visit
the Planned Parenthood website

24:56.843 --> 24:58.801
at PlannedParenthood.org.

24:58.845 --> 25:00.803
♪♪

25:00.847 --> 25:02.631
Thank you for listening.

25:02.675 --> 25:04.590
[ Door opens ]

25:04.633 --> 25:10.639
♪♪

25:10.683 --> 25:12.554
[ Exhales deeply ]

25:12.598 --> 25:14.643
♪♪

25:14.687 --> 25:18.908
Dude, how can you come back
to this place?

25:18.952 --> 25:20.997
[ Exhales sharply ]And after everything
that we went through...

25:21.041 --> 25:23.609
I would think

25:23.652 --> 25:26.089
that this might be the last
place you'd want to work.

25:26.133 --> 25:30.311
When I left here to go to
Stanford, it was the same thing.

25:30.354 --> 25:33.967
The diversity was not great,
but the difference was

25:34.010 --> 25:37.492
I took some classes
with a few Black professors.

25:37.536 --> 25:40.626
And I realized how much
one person can move the needle,

25:40.669 --> 25:45.152
which is exactly why we need
people like you to be involved.

25:45.195 --> 25:46.457
What do you mean?

25:46.501 --> 25:49.286
I want you to screen
your documentary here.

25:49.330 --> 25:52.159
I've seen it.
It's bold. It's challenging.

25:52.202 --> 25:55.728
It shows reality
without sugarcoating it.

25:55.771 --> 26:00.733
I think it's exactly what
the student body needs to see.

26:00.776 --> 26:02.386
What do you say?

26:02.430 --> 26:11.657
♪♪

26:11.700 --> 26:13.572
Hope you're not picturing
my face while you do that.

26:13.615 --> 26:15.574
[ Chuckles ] No.

26:15.617 --> 26:18.098
I just wanted to get
a head start on my next gig.

26:18.141 --> 26:19.839
Work ethic.

26:19.882 --> 26:23.582
Another thing that makes you
such a good business partner.

26:23.625 --> 26:25.975
I'm sorry
for leaving earlier.

26:26.019 --> 26:30.371
And I-I know
you mean well, Dad, but...

26:30.414 --> 26:33.113
I already did
the big restaurant.

26:33.156 --> 26:35.985
I worked nonstop
to make that dream work.

26:36.029 --> 26:38.248
And, yes,
I loved a part of it,

26:38.292 --> 26:41.600
but I also didn't sleep
for two years.

26:41.643 --> 26:44.211
Never stopped thinking
about the overhead

26:44.254 --> 26:46.561
or if we could afford
another month.

26:46.605 --> 26:48.389
I swear, I was happier
just cooking

26:48.432 --> 26:50.652
on that little food truck
in Miami.

26:50.696 --> 26:52.872
Hey, we made a hell of a meal
out of that food truck.

26:52.915 --> 26:54.525
Yeah, we did.

26:54.569 --> 26:56.745
[ Chuckles ]

26:56.789 --> 26:58.573
Hm.

26:58.617 --> 27:01.141
♪♪

27:01.184 --> 27:03.883
You know...

27:03.926 --> 27:07.277
Someday was Jon's
last gift to me.

27:07.321 --> 27:12.239
And I was devastated
when I lost it, but...

27:12.282 --> 27:15.198
being there today,
I realized that

27:15.242 --> 27:18.506
even if I could
have it back, I-I...

27:18.549 --> 27:19.768
I wouldn't want it.

27:21.291 --> 27:23.250
And I think that's
what hurt me the most --

27:23.293 --> 27:24.991
seeing that
what used to be the dream

27:25.034 --> 27:26.819
doesn't fit
who I am anymore.

27:26.862 --> 27:28.647
[ Chuckles ]

27:28.690 --> 27:30.039
I understand.

27:31.998 --> 27:34.609
I think I just jumped
at the opportunity

27:34.653 --> 27:38.874
to fix something for you
because --

27:38.918 --> 27:43.009
because I wasn't here
when it actually broke.

27:44.967 --> 27:47.274
I know, Dad.

27:47.317 --> 27:50.059
But, you know,
I think it's best that we --

27:50.103 --> 27:52.409
that we both look forward,
and not back.

27:52.453 --> 27:58.415
♪♪

27:58.459 --> 28:04.683
♪♪

28:06.728 --> 28:07.773
Wow.

28:08.861 --> 28:10.210
God, that was fast.

28:12.125 --> 28:14.040
No.

28:14.083 --> 28:17.173
Maggie, I'm the one
who's packing.

28:17.217 --> 28:19.132
Mr. Cutler fired me.

28:19.175 --> 28:23.223
♪♪

28:27.488 --> 28:29.925
What?
No, he ca-- he can't.

28:29.969 --> 28:31.927
He said if I couldn't control
my talent,

28:31.971 --> 28:34.277
then he would hire
someone who could.

28:34.321 --> 28:36.932
I mean,
after 10 years.

28:36.976 --> 28:39.065
Okay.
W-Why didn't you tell me

28:39.108 --> 28:41.067
about that
when we spoke earlier?

28:43.547 --> 28:46.463
Because I didn't want you to
censor yourself because of me.

28:48.683 --> 28:51.294
And I am so glad
that you didn't.

28:51.338 --> 28:54.167
You were amazing.

28:56.822 --> 28:59.650
No. Jane.
I can't believe this.

28:59.694 --> 29:01.783
I am gonna call him
and get your job back,

29:01.827 --> 29:04.307
and if he fires me in
the process, then so be it.

29:04.351 --> 29:05.961
Do not fall
on that sword.

29:07.746 --> 29:09.486
You keep your ratings up,

29:09.530 --> 29:11.619
and you will have
incredible leverage

29:11.662 --> 29:14.753
to keep doing the good work
you are doing here.

29:14.796 --> 29:16.276
Okay,
but what about you?

29:16.319 --> 29:18.800
I'll find my footing.
I always do.

29:18.844 --> 29:20.628
I know you will.
I-I just...

29:20.671 --> 29:23.022
I heard you got fired.

29:23.065 --> 29:26.155
Oh. Go ahead. Get your gloating
out of the way.

29:27.940 --> 29:29.855
Be nice not having you
as a boss.

29:29.898 --> 29:31.552
That's all you got?

29:31.595 --> 29:33.989
Geez. You really
could use a vacation.

29:35.251 --> 29:38.211
I meant it'll be nice
not having you as a boss

29:38.254 --> 29:40.213
because now I can ask you.

29:40.256 --> 29:43.346
Would you like to go with me
to Nantucket?

29:43.390 --> 29:45.696
I'm pretty sick of acting
like I don't like you.

29:45.740 --> 29:47.046
So what do you say?

29:47.089 --> 29:54.836
♪♪

29:54.880 --> 29:57.621
I, um...

29:57.665 --> 29:59.232
I say yes.

29:59.275 --> 30:00.624
[ Elevator bell dings ]

30:00.668 --> 30:04.933
♪♪

30:04.977 --> 30:06.021
Shall we?

30:06.065 --> 30:07.718
Yeah. Yeah.

30:07.762 --> 30:12.854
♪♪

30:12.898 --> 30:17.903
♪♪

30:19.556 --> 30:21.341
Dan?!

30:25.432 --> 30:27.303
[ Knock on door ]

30:30.524 --> 30:33.788
Ramen.
Uncooked.

30:33.832 --> 30:36.269
Oh, it's worse
than I thought.

30:36.312 --> 30:39.011
Or is it better?
It's tough to say.

30:40.882 --> 30:42.884
I feel like my whole life
is falling apart,

30:42.928 --> 30:45.931
and I can't do
anything about it.

30:45.974 --> 30:49.673
And if I try to fix it,
then everyone is yelling at me.

30:49.717 --> 30:51.675
And...

30:51.719 --> 30:53.460
I just can't do it.

30:53.503 --> 30:55.462
This never
should have happened.

30:55.505 --> 30:57.768
I know.

30:57.812 --> 31:00.989
I'm sorry for the unnatural way
that my voice carries.

31:02.512 --> 31:04.297
No.

31:04.340 --> 31:08.301
I mean that I never
should have gone to France.

31:08.344 --> 31:10.825
We just abandoned our lives
to go to Paris

31:10.869 --> 31:13.306
because that's what
my mom needed to do,

31:13.349 --> 31:16.962
and I was trying to be
the good son and put her first.

31:17.005 --> 31:19.442
But everything
got messed up.

31:19.486 --> 31:22.576
♪♪

31:22.619 --> 31:25.579
You're right.

31:25.622 --> 31:28.060
You haven't got to be
the kid you deserve to be.

31:30.497 --> 31:33.239
I know
you think Milo is bad.

31:33.282 --> 31:35.110
But I really believe
he was telling the truth

31:35.154 --> 31:37.025
when he said
he was just lonely.

31:39.593 --> 31:41.421
'Cause I was lonely, too.

31:41.464 --> 31:45.599
♪♪

31:45.642 --> 31:47.688
I'm sorry for
being pushy earlier.

31:47.731 --> 31:49.211
That wasn't helpful.

31:49.255 --> 31:53.085
But I am listening, now,
so you tell me what you need.

31:53.128 --> 31:56.436
I need you
to forgive him, too.

31:56.479 --> 31:59.134
I can't trust him again
without you backing me up,

31:59.178 --> 32:02.572
and I hate feeling like I have
to choose between you two.

32:05.662 --> 32:08.274
No.

32:08.317 --> 32:12.452
You don't ever have to choose
when it comes to me.

32:12.495 --> 32:15.063
No matter what, I'm --
I'm not going anywhere.

32:16.586 --> 32:17.936
You got that?

32:20.851 --> 32:22.505
You're stuck with me.

32:23.942 --> 32:25.813
This...

32:28.685 --> 32:31.427
It's stronger
than whatever...

32:31.471 --> 32:33.908
magical food glue
they use

32:33.952 --> 32:35.649
to bind these bricks.

32:35.692 --> 32:37.738
What is this, Dan?

32:37.781 --> 32:39.958
I don't know.
Yeah.

32:40.001 --> 32:41.960
[ Laughs ]

32:43.352 --> 32:46.094
Alright. Theo got bored
with that Lego an hour ago.

32:46.138 --> 32:47.878
Wanna tell me
what's going on?

32:47.922 --> 32:51.447
Why are you
avoiding Anna?

32:51.491 --> 32:53.145
Because.

32:53.188 --> 32:57.323
If I'm being honest,
I was probably relieved

32:57.366 --> 33:00.979
to have an excuse not to
stay over at her place tonight.

33:02.806 --> 33:06.027
She wants me to...
you know...

33:06.071 --> 33:07.376
stay over.

33:09.335 --> 33:11.250
Oh.

33:11.293 --> 33:12.773
I see the problem now.

33:12.816 --> 33:15.080
Your really hot girlfriend
wants to have sex with you.

33:15.123 --> 33:16.559
I can see
why you're upset.

33:16.603 --> 33:18.997
Ha ha.

33:19.040 --> 33:20.563
I'm just --

33:20.607 --> 33:25.307
I'm very nervous about
performing since...my injury.

33:27.483 --> 33:29.050
You did pretty well
with me.

33:29.094 --> 33:31.835
[ Chuckles ] But you knew
what I was like before.

33:31.879 --> 33:35.578
With Anna,
it's all new, and...

33:35.622 --> 33:37.363
I don't know.

33:37.406 --> 33:40.235
It's a new person.
There's a lot to figure out.

33:40.279 --> 33:43.108
I mean, I can relate.
Trust me.

33:47.851 --> 33:48.852
Can I ask you something?

33:48.896 --> 33:50.811
Yeah, of course.

33:53.292 --> 33:55.729
Was it me...

33:55.772 --> 33:58.688
that sent you on...

34:00.734 --> 34:02.388
...your journey?

34:03.911 --> 34:06.609
Edward Saville, are you asking
if you ruined men for me?

34:06.653 --> 34:08.959
[ Laughs ]

34:09.003 --> 34:11.136
I promise --

34:11.179 --> 34:12.311
you had nothing
to do with it.

34:14.269 --> 34:18.099
I was never
not attracted to you.

34:20.362 --> 34:22.756
It's just now
I'm attracted to her.

34:24.845 --> 34:28.327
I mean,
I wasn't even aware

34:28.370 --> 34:33.114
I could feel this way
about women until now.

34:33.158 --> 34:37.162
That's a relief --
for me and my fragile man ego.

34:37.205 --> 34:39.338
[ Laughs ]
Thank you.

34:39.381 --> 34:44.082
But I feel you on how hard it is
to go there with someone new.

34:45.561 --> 34:46.954
You do?

34:46.997 --> 34:49.478
But y-- you, like...

34:49.522 --> 34:51.263
know your way
around town.

34:51.306 --> 34:53.526
[ Chuckles ] You were born
and raised there.

34:53.569 --> 34:55.571
Oh, my God.I'm -- [ Chuckles ]

34:55.615 --> 34:59.619
Just a tourist with an outdated
"Frommer's" travel guide.

34:59.662 --> 35:01.925
Oh, hmm.
You have all the DL

35:01.969 --> 35:05.059
on all the cool spots
the locals go to, right?

35:05.103 --> 35:08.323
You'd think, but it just makes
the pressure so much higher.

35:08.367 --> 35:10.717
Like, I should know
what I'm doing, and I don't.

35:10.760 --> 35:13.589
[ Both laughing ]

35:13.633 --> 35:15.635
[ Both sigh ]

35:17.550 --> 35:19.378
Look at us.

35:19.421 --> 35:20.901
We're doing pretty great.

35:20.944 --> 35:23.947
Yeah. We are.

35:23.991 --> 35:27.081
Although...
I feel obligated to tell you

35:27.125 --> 35:28.430
that you're not gonna
help matters with Anna

35:28.474 --> 35:31.041
by spending the night
at your ex-wife's house.

35:32.434 --> 35:35.611
Go to her
and rock her world.

35:35.655 --> 35:37.526
[ Chuckles ]

35:37.570 --> 35:39.311
[ Both chuckle ]

35:41.748 --> 35:43.097
[ Laughter ]
Yeah.

35:43.141 --> 35:44.446
It's a good thing you decided
to go into education

35:44.490 --> 35:46.361
because you made
the worst Tweedledum ever.

35:46.405 --> 35:49.364
Ah! Well, at least
I didn't ask Alice to the prom

35:49.408 --> 35:51.018
while wearing
that Cheshire Cat costume.

35:51.061 --> 35:53.281
Hey, she still
said yes, okay?

35:53.325 --> 35:56.371
Listen, I have a meeting
with the Dean right now,

35:56.415 --> 35:58.417
but I'll see you
on Friday?

35:58.460 --> 35:59.766
That's right.

35:59.809 --> 36:03.030
Rome Howard.
[ Chuckles ]

36:03.073 --> 36:05.467
I heard you were
visiting us today.

36:05.511 --> 36:08.905
♪♪

36:08.949 --> 36:11.430
Uh, Mr. Dennings.
[ Chuckles ]

36:11.473 --> 36:13.649
Didn't realize
you still taught here.

36:13.693 --> 36:16.478
Oh,
I don't teach anymore.

36:16.522 --> 36:18.393
I'm the Dean now.

36:18.437 --> 36:19.960
Uh, if you'll excuse us,

36:20.003 --> 36:22.397
I really need to steal
Mr. Washington.

36:22.441 --> 36:24.660
Uh, but it's good
to see you again, Rome.

36:25.922 --> 36:28.229
So, what I was thinking...

36:28.273 --> 36:33.060
♪♪

36:39.632 --> 36:42.025
[ Doorbell rings ]

36:47.466 --> 36:49.207
Hey.

36:50.860 --> 36:52.558
Thank you for
putting up with me.

36:52.601 --> 36:55.430
It was wrong of me
to cancel on you,

36:55.474 --> 36:57.954
and the truth is, Theo
didn't really need me there.

37:00.479 --> 37:02.916
Does it help
that I brought dessert?

37:04.483 --> 37:07.225
We got, uh, apple pie,

37:07.268 --> 37:10.228
uh, cheesecake that has
12 different flavors

37:10.271 --> 37:12.795
divided by little
paper partitions,

37:12.839 --> 37:15.929
and one extremely yellow
pound cake.

37:17.060 --> 37:21.195
Wow. You baked 12 different
individual cheesecake slices

37:21.239 --> 37:24.067
and then...
partitioned them?

37:24.111 --> 37:25.808
It's the least
I could do.

37:30.204 --> 37:33.251
I was feeling nervous
about our date

37:33.294 --> 37:37.429
because I haven't had
much experience in the bedroom

37:37.472 --> 37:39.735
since my injury.

37:39.779 --> 37:43.435
And I like you. A lot.

37:43.478 --> 37:45.915
And you're right --
it is time.

37:45.959 --> 37:48.178
And...

37:48.222 --> 37:51.921
I'm extremely,
really excited.

37:53.401 --> 37:55.751
Also, it seems like
things go better here

37:55.795 --> 37:57.492
if I show up unannounced.

37:57.536 --> 37:59.320
[ Laughs ]

37:59.364 --> 38:01.888
Uh, I don't know
about better.

38:01.931 --> 38:05.370
I mean, you did miss out
on a very nice dress.

38:05.413 --> 38:07.937
And matching lingerie
underneath.

38:07.981 --> 38:10.549
But I'm sure
we can make it work.

38:13.465 --> 38:15.118
Lead the way.

38:15.162 --> 38:23.344
♪♪

38:23.388 --> 38:26.391
[ Bell jingles ]Yeah, we have the
St. Matthews' confirmation

38:26.434 --> 38:29.698
in two weeks, and half
of their budget is wine.

38:29.742 --> 38:31.961
[ Laughs ] Yeah, they really
love their blood of Christ.

38:32.005 --> 38:33.311
[ Horn honks ][ Gasps ]

38:35.400 --> 38:38.272
Um, Val, I'm gonna
have to call you back.

38:39.795 --> 38:41.754
Ta-da!
What's this?

38:41.797 --> 38:43.364
This is me
taking a gamble

38:43.408 --> 38:45.845
on being a better
business partner, alright?

38:45.888 --> 38:48.064
It's just a test drive.
We can totally return it.

38:49.414 --> 38:51.459
But this morning,
you mentioned that you enjoyed

38:51.503 --> 38:54.288
cooking on the set,
and I got this idea, huh?

38:54.332 --> 38:58.379
We could fix her up and drive it
to any job that you book.

38:58.423 --> 39:01.077
Keep it small.
Keep it about the food.

39:03.906 --> 39:07.257
[ Chuckles ]
It's perfect.

39:07.301 --> 39:08.694
Yeah?
Yeah.

39:08.737 --> 39:11.610
Yeah? Hey, we could even
spray-paint across the front

39:11.653 --> 39:13.307
"Ease Catering."

39:13.351 --> 39:15.004
Okay, actually, I have
a different idea for a name.

39:15.048 --> 39:16.702
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

39:16.745 --> 39:19.444
Uh, what do you think about
"Starting Fresh Catering"?

39:22.185 --> 39:23.665
I love it.

39:23.709 --> 39:25.058
It's even got
the "teh" sound.

39:25.101 --> 39:27.321
[ Laughs ]

39:27.365 --> 39:29.715
Hey, I have my test drive
for 20 more minutes.

39:29.758 --> 39:30.933
Wanna take her for a spin?

39:30.977 --> 39:32.631
Regina:
I'd love to! Yes!

39:32.674 --> 39:34.154
Alright.

39:34.197 --> 39:35.851
Clutch sticks a little bit,
but...

39:35.895 --> 39:38.898
she could be real pretty
if we fix her up.

39:38.941 --> 39:41.683
[ Chuckling ] And then
they make this guy the Dean!

39:41.727 --> 39:43.642
Wait. What?!

39:43.685 --> 39:46.427
Wow! I can't believe
that guy still works there!

39:46.471 --> 39:47.907
I guess all the dinosaurs
aren'textinct.

39:47.950 --> 39:49.778
[ Laughs ] For real.

39:49.822 --> 39:51.301
You know, you're gonna go with
me to that screening on Friday.

39:51.345 --> 39:52.738
Oh, I'd be happy to,

39:52.781 --> 39:54.522
but I'm surprised you still
want to go through with it.

39:54.566 --> 39:55.741
Of course I do.

39:55.784 --> 39:58.526
Dude, we're gonna
walk up on the stage,

39:58.570 --> 40:01.529
and I'm gonna tell them
that my film about racism

40:01.573 --> 40:04.967
was inspired by their
poor excuse for a Dean.

40:05.011 --> 40:08.231
I cannot wait to see the look
on his face when I call him out.

40:08.275 --> 40:11.017
Huh?

40:11.060 --> 40:13.454
When I'm done, that place
is nevergonna be the same.

40:13.498 --> 40:16.457
♪ Sweet disposition

40:16.501 --> 40:20.766
Gary:
[ Sighs ] Things didn't quite go
according to plan today.

40:20.809 --> 40:23.421
Danny's at the movies
with Milo right now.

40:23.464 --> 40:26.467
I guess somehow he worked things
out with that little D-bag.

40:26.511 --> 40:29.992
But I told him I would be
supportive no matter what,

40:30.036 --> 40:31.994
which means I'm removing
the word "douchebag"

40:32.038 --> 40:34.780
from my vocabulary
starting now.

40:34.823 --> 40:36.477
Wow.
It only took you 20 years

40:36.521 --> 40:37.826
to catch up
to the rest of us.

40:37.870 --> 40:39.741
I'm soproud of you.

40:39.785 --> 40:41.743
Yeah. [ Groans ]

40:43.528 --> 40:45.268
[ Sighs ]

40:47.009 --> 40:49.925
You know, I am really
proud of you, though.

40:49.969 --> 40:51.971
I know it meant a lot
to Danny.

40:54.060 --> 40:57.280
Well, when I was waiting at home
earlier for Danny to get back,

40:57.324 --> 41:01.023
my favorite
talk-radio show host

41:01.067 --> 41:03.069
reminded me that
we have to let people

41:03.112 --> 41:04.418
make their own choices,

41:04.462 --> 41:06.899
even if we don't agree
with them...

41:06.942 --> 41:09.336
and that
if you love someone,

41:09.379 --> 41:11.817
you just gotta be there
for them.

41:11.860 --> 41:14.384
It's funny. I thought
it would be easy to let go.

41:14.428 --> 41:17.997
But knowing that he's probably
gonna get hurt and...

41:18.040 --> 41:19.302
♪ Our rights, our wrongs

41:19.346 --> 41:21.609
It's excruciating.

41:21.653 --> 41:23.655
He's not even my kid.

41:23.698 --> 41:26.396
♪ A kiss, a cry

41:26.440 --> 41:28.529
Maybe not.

41:28.573 --> 41:31.097
But you were a really great dad
to him today.

41:31.140 --> 41:34.013
♪♪

41:34.056 --> 41:35.362
Mm.

41:35.405 --> 41:40.106
♪ 'Cause I'll be coming over

41:40.149 --> 41:43.152
♪♪

41:43.196 --> 41:44.502
[ Sighs ]

41:44.545 --> 41:46.678
♪ And while our blood's
still young ♪

41:46.721 --> 41:49.463
♪ Just stay there

41:49.507 --> 41:51.073
♪♪

41:51.117 --> 41:53.423
Hello, Maggie.

41:53.467 --> 41:57.079
♪ 'Cause I'll be coming over

41:57.123 --> 41:58.428
Thank you
for squeezing me in.

41:58.472 --> 42:00.735
I know it was
very last-minute.

42:00.779 --> 42:02.607
Of course.

42:02.650 --> 42:04.347
It's still another month

42:04.391 --> 42:06.045
before your next
cancer screening, though.

42:06.088 --> 42:07.742
Is everything okay?

42:07.786 --> 42:09.527
♪ It's so young, it runs

42:09.570 --> 42:11.267
Totally.

42:11.311 --> 42:15.010
I actually wanted to talk
to you about...

42:15.054 --> 42:17.317
♪ Won't stop till it's over

42:19.754 --> 42:21.582
...me having a baby.

42:21.626 --> 42:24.237
♪ Won't stop to surrender

42:29.851 --> 42:39.469
♪♪

42:39.513 --> 42:48.827
♪♪

42:48.870 --> 42:58.184
♪♪
